<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="F" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Flatterer" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Flatterer,</orth> 1) one who flatters, a fawner, wheedler: <bibl n="shak. son 112.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 112, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.1.100" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 1, 100</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.1.100" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 1, 100</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r2 4.306.100" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 306</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.4.31" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 4, 31</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.9.43" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 9, 43</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 3.1.45" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 45</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 1.1.58" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. I, 1, 58</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 1.1.58" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. I, 1, 58</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tim 1.2.83" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 2, 83</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 3.2.72" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 72</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.206" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 206</bibl> etc. <bibl n="shak. jc 2.1.206" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. II, 1, 206</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 3.1.193" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 193</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 4.3.91" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 91</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 5.1.44" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 44</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 5.1.44" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 44</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lr 2.2.117" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. II, 2, 117</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 1.2.60" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 2, 60</bibl>.<lb />2) that which gratifies and deludes with hopes: <cit><quote>and fear to find mine eye too great a f. for my mind,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 1.5.328" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 5, 328</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>if thine eye be not a f., come thou on my side,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.271" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 4, 271</bibl></cit>. Quibbling: <cit><quote>I will put off hope and keep it no longer for my f.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.3.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. III, 3, 8</bibl></cit>. cf. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.2.69" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 2, 69</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>